AB  - This paper formulates and estimates a dynamic model to investigate the characteristics of the cost function of Australian Permanent Building Societies. While the results suggest that the societies adjust costs quickly to long-run levels, the modelling of cost dynamics is shown to have a significant influence on estimates of scale economies, and on the identification of the timing of shifts in the cost frontier and changes in the growth of total factor productivity.
